<TITLE> Portlink resumes operations Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 30 (bdnews24.com) - Portlink Logistics, a private inland container depot operator, resumes operations Sunday after three months of suspension. But the company has been set a condition that it has to cut noise pollutionan issue that had led Bangladesh Military Academy to file a compliant with the customs authorities. Portlink, located close to Bangladesh Military Aacademy in Bhatiary, stopped operations on Oct 23 last year on objection that its activities caused sound pollution. "We have decided to allow the private ICD operator to resume its operations on condition that sound pollution is reduced," Md Nasir Uddin, customs commissioner (import), told bdnews24.com Wednesday. Earlier, the commissioner had a meeting with ICD officials at the Chittagong Customs building. He said the company would be issued a letter of permission Thursday to restart the activities if it signed an undertaking to comply with the directive. Ahsanul Haque Chowdhury, executive director of Portlink, told bdnews24.com that the company had been asked to take measures to minimse sound pollution. He said his company would meet the condition. The meeting was also attended by the officials of the Chittagong Cantonment executive board, members of C&F Agents Association, BGMEA representatives and shipping agents. bdnews2
